## Enumerations

### enum  {#a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum WPDCheckMode ">
Mechanism to add runtime checking of devirtualization decisions, optionally trapping or falling back to indirect call on any that are not correct.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421ac9d3e887722f2bc482bcca9d41c512af" />
<EnumerationListItem name="None">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421a178e499decd0c21272bc34e4b3056eab" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Trap">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421aad98505ec3c6cabbb406c37037410854" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Fallback">

</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

Trapping mode is useful for debugging undefined behavior leading to failures with WPD. Fallback mode is useful for ensuring safety when whole program visibility may be compromised.

Definition at line <a href="#l00205">205</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/wholeprogramdevirt-cpp">WholeProgramDevirt.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>

Definition at line <a href="#l00195">195</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/wholeprogramdevirt-cpp">WholeProgramDevirt.cpp</a>.

### WholeProgramDevirtKeepUnreachableFunction {#a92e98b87a580ee2727a894cafc57a73e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>cl::opt&lt; bool &gt; WholeProgramDevirtKeepUnreachableFunction(&quot;wholeprogramdevirt-keep-unreachable-function&quot;, cl::desc(&quot;Regard unreachable functions as possible devirtualize targets.&quot;), cl::Hidden, cl::init(true))</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
With Clang, a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor is emitted as a <code>llvm.trap</code> intrinsic followed by an unreachable IR instruction.

In the context of whole program devirtualization, the deleting destructor of a pure virtual class won&#39;t be invoked by the source code so safe to skip as a devirtualize target.

However, not all unreachable functions are safe to skip. In some cases, the program intends to run such functions and terminate, for instance, a unit test may run a death test. A non-test program might (or allowed to) invoke such functions to report failures (whether/when it&#39;s a good practice or not is a different topic).

This option is enabled to keep an unreachable function as a possible devirtualize target to conservatively keep the program behavior.

TODO: Make a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor precisely identifiable in Clang&#39;s codegen for more devirtualization in LLVM.

Definition at line <a href="#l00187">187</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/wholeprogramdevirt-cpp">WholeProgramDevirt.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

This is needed to support legacy tests that don&#39;t contain !vcall&#95;visibility metadata (the mere presense of type tests previously implied hidden visibility).

<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This pass implements whole program optimization of virtual calls in cases</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// where we know (via !type metadata) that the list of callees is fixed. This</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// includes the following:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - Single implementation devirtualization: if a virtual call has a single</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   possible callee, replace all calls with a direct call to that callee.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - Virtual constant propagation: if the virtual function&#39;s return type is an</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   integer &lt;=64 bits and all possible callees are readnone, for each class and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   each list of constant arguments: evaluate the function, store the return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   value alongside the virtual table, and rewrite each virtual call as a load</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   from the virtual table.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - Uniform return value optimization: if the conditions for virtual constant</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   propagation hold and each function returns the same constant value, replace</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   each virtual call with that constant.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - Unique return value optimization for i1 return values: if the conditions</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   for virtual constant propagation hold and a single vtable&#39;s function</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   returns 0, or a single vtable&#39;s function returns 1, replace each virtual</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   call with a comparison of the vptr against that vtable&#39;s address.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This pass is intended to be used during the regular and thin LTO pipelines:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// During regular LTO, the pass determines the best optimization for each</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// virtual call and applies the resolutions directly to virtual calls that are</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - Export phase: this is run during the thin link over a single merged module</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><Highlight kind="comment">/// With Clang, a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor is emitted as a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#96;llvm.trap&#96; intrinsic followed by an unreachable IR instruction. In the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><Highlight kind="comment">/// context of whole program devirtualization, the deleting destructor of a pure</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><Highlight kind="comment">/// virtual class won&#39;t be invoked by the source code so safe to skip as a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><Highlight kind="comment">/// devirtualize target.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><Highlight kind="comment">/// However, not all unreachable functions are safe to skip. In some cases, the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><Highlight kind="comment">/// program intends to run such functions and terminate, for instance, a unit</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><Highlight kind="comment">/// test may run a death test. A non-test program might (or allowed to) invoke</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><Highlight kind="comment">/// such functions to report failures (whether/when it&#39;s a good practice or not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is a different topic).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This option is enabled to keep an unreachable function as a possible</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><Highlight kind="comment">/// devirtualize target to conservatively keep the program behavior.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><Highlight kind="comment">/// TODO: Make a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor precisely identifiable</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01889" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1889"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// ends of the object.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1891"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;&amp;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/target">Target</a> : TargetsForSlot) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1900"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (std::min(TotalPaddingBefore, TotalPaddingAfter) &gt; 128)</Highlight></CodeLine>
